As part of my rebranding/overhaul thing, I'm migrating my blog over to a subdomain, and creating a new Kaffie.bit homepage. However, I realize that there are many links back to my blog, which really point to kaffie.bit. So to resolve that, I'm having the main kaffie.bit page redirect blog post urls to the appropriate post. Here's the snippet of code that does that.

```
var x = location.search.replace(/wrapper_nonce=.+/g,'');
if(x != "?" && x != null)
{
window.top.location.replace("/1N6zp6jCXPBktNMPfe7UJBpQGyfCq7k2M8/"+x);
}
```

I might have to end up changing it if the new homepage uses get values. But that's what I'm using for the time being. Short, sweet, and to the point.

Bootstrapper plugin isn't working? I've enabled it, but I can't add myself as a tracker, and I can't seem to connect to @Daniell Mesquita:'s boostrapper node either. I've tried with both ipv4 and cjdns ipv6. Neither work.

